[2026-03-18T17:43:01.229Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Unify retention into declarative lifecycle policies\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: maintenance\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (6/3)\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:59:39 AM\n\n## Description\nretention.ts and auditRetentionPolicy.ts independently implement the exact same algorithm: compute a date cutoff, chunked-delete with PURGE_CHUNK_SIZE=5000, WAL-bounded iteration, and daily interval scheduling. Extract a single RetentionPolicy class parameterized by {table, cutoffColumn, chunkSize, safetyFraction?, preDeleteAggregator?}. Each table registers its lifecycle declaratively rather than re-implementing the loop.\n\n## Reasoning\nTwo files contain structurally identical code that will diverge over time (the audit version already added a safety-cap fraction that the execution version lacks). Unifying means bug fixes, safety improvements, and observability enhancements apply everywhere at once. This is the classic moment where a pattern solidifies into an abstraction.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94e86188-551c-4f12-8c24-5d2ac7eddc18","uuid":"bc3476ac-80d9-4307-ba18-21ac7b0bf8bf","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:43:01.147Z","isSynthetic":true}
