[2026-03-18T17:47:12.169Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0193AA8aBahbriewEZ7TscHL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All types pass cleanly. Here's what was done:\n\n**New file: `retentionPolicy.ts`** — A single `RetentionPolicy` class parameterized by `{table, chunkSize?, deleteFilter?}`. It reads `timestampColumn` and `maxPurgeFraction` from `TABLE_REGISTRY` at construction, then provides one `purge(db, cutoff, logger)` method that handles the safety-fraction check and chunked delete with event-loop yields.\n\n**Changes to `retention.ts`** — Replaced ~100 lines of hand-rolled purge logic (`_ret_ids` temp table, manual chunked delete loops, separate safety checks per table) with three declarative policy instances:\n- `execPolicy` — `persona_executions` with terminal-status filter\n- `eventsPolicy` — `persona_events` excluding stuck statuses\n- `stuckEventsPolicy` — `persona_events` for stuck rows (7x retention cutoff)\n\nThe `runTenantRetention` function collapsed from 100 lines to 10 lines of `policy.purge()` calls.\n\n**Changes to `auditRetentionPolicy.ts`** — Replaced the duplicated safety-check + `AuditLog.purgeOlderThan` delegation with a single `auditPolicy.purge()` call via `AuditLog.getDb()`.\n\n**Changes to `auditLog.ts`** — Added `getDb()` accessor so `AuditRetentionPolicy` can pass the raw DB to the shared policy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":65002,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94e86188-551c-4f12-8c24-5d2ac7eddc18","uuid":"3c96dda4-9221-40c5-8ef0-28e5a79ddb3c"}
